The White House Office of National Drug Control Policy (ONDCP) has released the Trump Administration's Fiscal Year 2021 National Drug Control Budget. The budget requests $35.7 billion for counter-drug efforts, an increase of $94 million from the previous year. The request includes $18.6 billion for prevention and treatment efforts and $17.1 billion for domestic law enforcement, interdiction, and international drug control efforts. The budget aims to achieve the goals and objectives of the National Drug Control Strategy. The request funds drug control priorities across various government departments and agencies, including $7 billion to address the opioid crisis. The Trump Administration had previously released its 2020 National Drug Control Strategy.